  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The sons of Judah,.... The genealogy begins with him, though the fourth son of Jacob; because, as Kimchi says, this book treats chiefly of the kings of Judah; but rather not only because Jesse and David sprang from him, but also the King Messiah: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Er, and Onan, and Shelah, which three were born unto him of the daughter of Shua the Canaanitess; see Genesis 38:2, ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Er, and Onan, and Shelah, which three were born unto him of the daughter of Shua the Canaanitess; see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Genesis 38:2",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and Er, the firstborn of Judah, was evil in the sight of the Lord; because he did that which was evil: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and he slew him; he died by the immediate hand of God, and so his brother Onan, being wicked also, Genesis 38:7. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and he slew him; he died by the immediate hand of God, and so his brother Onan, being wicked also, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Genesis 38:7",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
